17/07/2007
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Retired Serbian General Vlastimir Djordjevic pleaded not guilty Monday (July 16th) to charges of war crimes against ethnic Albanians during the Serb invasion in Kosovo in the first six months of 1999. 
At the time, Djordjevic was Serbia's deputy interior minister and head of the State Security Agency. 
Indicted by the UN tribunal in October 2003, Djordjevic was arrested in Budva, Montenegro, last month. 
(B92, RTS, RTRS, Tanjug, AP - 16/07/07)
